09/06/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The United States has offered to donate 20 Huey 2 helicopters to the Bulgarian Army, Chief of General Staff Gen Nikola Kolev said on Sunday (8 June). 
He made the comments after returning from a seven-day visit to the United States at the invitation of his US counterpart, Gen Richard Myers. 
According to the proposal, the US Army would provide the helicopters and related equipment and would cover the cost of the modernisation of the equipment. 
(24 Chassa, Standart, Trud - 09/06/03; BTA - 08/06/03)
